                <note rend="inline" type="source">885.73/151: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Riddle</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-07-01T19:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 1, 1922—7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 2—12:05 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>40. Your no. 25, June 28, 6 p.m.<note n="63" xml:id="d276fn63">Not
                        printed.</note> Minister of the Interior and Procurador del Tesoro Lopez
                    assured me today that they would favor granting permission to any American cable
                    company to lay a cable to Brazil, and they felt sure that Argentine Government
                    could have no objection; but that administrative measures to make this binding
                    would probably require six weeks to two months although no congressional action
                    is necessary. Lopez stated that in his opinion article 13 was a precarious
                        concession<note n="64" xml:id="d276fn64">i.e., the privilege was held during
                        the pleasure of the grantor.</note> for the reason that no term was
                    specified and could therefore be rescinded by Congress, and that article 17
                    would not prove bar to the laying of a cable by any company.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Riddle</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
